I should have guessed. It's time for the annual Pittsburgh Penguins whine a thon. Bowman was complaning about cheap shots by the Devils in Game 1. I'm sorry, Mr. Hockey, but you're not the only one who's been taking cheap shot after cheap-shot.

The Penguins have been outscored by a combined total of 11-3 in the first two games of the series. They've been shut out in both games. The Penguins are 0-2 in their last three games, and they've lost four of their past five. That's not good. And it's a trend that's going to continue. This is a team that has been playing poorly for a while now. There's no reason to think they're going anywhere. But they are going nowhere. So, what's the solution?
